title: Has Blackpink had plastic surgery? - Quora

response.answer_text: All of them had plastic surgery but unfortunately a lot of people do not notice the difference on their faces, or they just deny it. I would like to add, judging from their pre-debut photos they had their procedure when they were mid-teen (which is legal and common in South Korea) and they are still doing minor changes to their faces. I believe they have done more procedures to their face than what I have wrote down. [LISA] • Nosejob (Side profile)  Her nose DOES NOT curve like a normal nose, nobody is born with a nose that perfectly curves upwards, she had nose bridge fillers to achieve that, even a nose job doesn’t curve your nose like that. (Nose Width)   Photos are self explanatory, her nose thinned down and became more defined and pointy, she used to have a flat nose and wide nostrils that were round however now she has a pointy nose tip and pointy nostrils, her nose as well became wonky. Her nose job even caused her smile lines to be wider. She also has a typical nose job nose, you don’t even need to see the before photo to know she had a procedure, her nose job wasn’t properly done, it doesn’t look natural. (Scars)   Those are scars due to the stitching. (Nose Wonkiness)  Her nose job is very poorly done. Uneven nose, triangle shaped nose and inverted nostrils which are usually caused by either bad surgeries or cheap ones. She’s very lucky her nose wasn’t completely botched because a lot of people are unable to breathe with a nose similar to hers. (Nose bridge fillers)  • Epicanthoplasty & Blepharoplasty & Canthoplasty   What Epicanthoplasty does is widen the eyes and makes it proportional to your eye distances, it involves cutting the eye corners and you can see Lisa’s inner eye corner is much wider and outer eye corner was stretched outwards which caused her bottom eye lid to be more straighter. What Blepharoplasty does is remove excess skin above the eye which tightens the skin and reduces the skin from drooping downwards which is why you can see her eyelid is higher and deeper. • Chin implant  She had a chin implant in 2016, as she grew up her chin was gradually receding (judging from her pre-debut photos) then all of a sudden her chin became augmented • Skin bleaching (Chances are she had injections since most surgeons bleach skin using injections in Korea)   These photos of her are not whitewashed, they are unedited photos of her. Either way whitewashed or not her skin was still bleached and she whitewashes herself on her Instagram which makes me believe more she intentionally whitened her skin.The only photo that is filtered is the baby photo since old cameras would automatically filter you so she is darker in real life than the photo. Some people need to understand that just because you bleach your skin does not mean you are going to be snow white, you can even bleach your skin to a different tone of your color - I say this since people are debating her skin bleaching because she is not pale white but “tan” (even though she isn’t tan). • Lip fillers   Her lips would change constantly, sometimes they would be more than double the size than before or they would be thin, you can see in the photo that her lips seems to be swollen (clearly she had fresh fillers) and her lips are wider. • Lip corner lift  I thought it was due to her lip fillers that her lip corner was lifted but no, it looks like she had her lip corners lifted and they were not done correctly, only 1 side is lifted more than the other side which caused her lip corners to be asymmetrical, you can see pre-debut her lip corners were the exact same. • Cheek fillers I noticed she takes cheek fillers once in a while because sometimes her cheeks look unnaturally huge then her cheeks becomes thin and defined. This isn’t normal and it happens consistently. Despite getting buccal fat removal, she sometimes prefer bigger cheeks for specific looks which I noticed with the lip fillers as well.  This is an example photo of her cheek fillers, where it is circled in red is where you can see without the cheek fillers her cheekbones are visible and her cheeks are more hollow, but with cheek fillers her cheeks are round and her cheekbones are not visible. There are some points where she would take too much where it becomes very visible and unnatural. • Buccal fat removal  She had buccal fat removal which I think it’s quite obvious, during debut she used to have round puffy cheeks which took the attention of a lot of people then after their hiatus her entire cheeks structure changed. Her face became much more defined including her cheekbones. The hiatus was the perfect time due to the fact of how long it takes to heal after the procedure. • Jawline fillers  Since around 2019 she’s been starting to take jawline fillers which gives you a define jawline, you can see before she used to have a soft jawline. [JISOO] • Epicanthoplasty & Lateral Canthoplasty  She has done surgeries to her eyes in order to enlarge them and reshape them. The biggest giveaway is her high school photo after joining the company versus her school photo before going into the company. [ROSÉ] • Epicanthoplasty & Lateral Canthoplasty  Her smile on the right was a lot wider than the one on the left so no it’s not because she was smiling that her eyes were small. • Rhinoplasty (Sideprofile)  (Nose Width)  (Nose bridge fillers)  [JENNIE] • Blepharoplasty & Cathoplasty  • Lips Augmentation  • Non surgical rhinoplasty This part would be added later. ————————————————————————————————————— I personally think plastic surgery was mandatory but then they had procedures themselves with permission from the company so I do not think this is all on the company for their surgeries. REGARDING THE RESTRICTIONS: BLACKPINK’s Jisoo And Rosé Talk About Strict Restrictions Under YG EntertainmentThings That Trainees Need To Give Up To Be A Part Of YG, As Told By YG Artists They have made it clear NUMEROUS TIMES since debut they can break any rules with permission yet people are still bringing up that they are not allowed to do anything restricted, including plastic surgery. They admitted to breaking those rules listed. After those interviews they broke many rules such as drinking numerous times, dating, travelling numerous times and driving. Suhyun (from AKMU which is under YG) even admitted YG suggested for her to get plastic surgery, she said this in 2016 which is the same year of BLACKPINK’s debut. If they are willing to offer a non idol to have surgery imagine what they do to their idols.

response.answer_text: I wanted to answer this question since I am studying cosmetology and plastic surgery. Looking at Blackpink’s predebut photos, right away I can deduce that all the members of Blackpink have had plastic surgery. However, please remember that although I am saying this based on careful thought and analysis, this is in no way the absolute truth! Edit: Some people seem to think that I am hating on Blackpink and picking out random assumptions of them having plastic surgery. I assure you, that is not the case. I have studied each member for a long time, and I am currently studying cosmetology and plastic surgery. I have minds to become a plastic surgeon, so I am not just nitpicking on Blackpink to hate on them. I do not think that plastic surgery is wrong and for people who do think so, I kindly recommend to click off this page. I don’t know why some Blinks think that plastic surgery is a terrible thing; they act like it’s a sin to even assume that Blackpink has had surgery. Anyways, sorry for the long introduction, if you still wish to read my answer, go ahead! Jisoo   I would say Jisoo has had Canthoplasty and Blepharoplasty. She probably reshaped her eyes by taking fat from her upper eyelids and lifting and tightening the outer corners of her eyes. Her eyes are bigger, and she has noticeably less fat on her upper eyelids. Jisoo has also had an Epicanthoplasty, where she lifted the inner corners of her eyes to make them more youthful and brighter. Her eyes are also elongated. I also think Jisoo fixed her nose to slightly point downwards (upturned noses are greatly disliked by Koreans). More proof Jisoo has altered her eyes:   She definitely has enhanced her double eyelid. It is very rare for someone to naturally have Jisoo’s extremely even and puffy double eyelids she has now. Her eyes before are eyes like Rose’s right now. Jennie     Jennie has had a cat-eye lift. Like Jisoo, she has had a double eyelid surgery and her eye shape is wider and longer. She also has had lip fillers:  Predebut Jennie’s lip   Jennie’s lips now (she had both her lips done, but especially her upper lip) More proof of her lip fillers: Before    After (look at how her lips are twice her size. Her lips also look a little wobbly.)    Let’s take a look at these photos again:   Now, Jennie’s nose clearly looks more pinched at the center. I think Jennie slimmed the tip of her nose (a nasal obstruction rhinoplasty.) When she smiles, it’s more obvious, because the tip of her nose looks very thin and pinched compared to her nostrils. Rosé      Rose has had a double eyelid surgery and a Blepharoplasty (taking fat from upper eyelids.) Now, sometimes double eyelids do naturally occur as you grow older (like my parents) so I can’t confirm for sure that Rose got double eyelids through surgery. But judging from her predebut photos, Rose had a lot of fat on her upper eyelids, like a lot. So it would have been harder for her to get natural double lids. Also, Rose uses double eyelid tape, because her double eyelids are in different places (compare 2nd to last and last picture.) Let’s look at these photos again:   Rose has definitely had rhinoplasty. The tip of her nose is less bulbous and her nostrils are slimmer and they point upward. Look at Rose’s face shape in the two pictues above again, then also look at these photos:    Yes, the angles might be different, but it’s obvious Rose had a chubbier face before. She probably has had a Buccal Fat Removal or a cheek liposuction which slims down round cheeks for a slimmer face. Rose’s face is noticeably longer, slimmer and her jaw is way more defined, another way to see if someone has had Buccal Fat Removal . Rose has also probably had genioplasty (elongating the chin) if you compare these photos, her chin is longer now than it was before. Also take a look at these side profiles:    It looks like Rose gradually make her nose slimmer and taller (reduction rhinoplasty.) Lisa     Right away we can tell Lisa has had rhinoplasty. Lisa has slimmed down her nose bridge, made the nostrils slimmer, and made the tip of the nose less bulbous. Like Jisoo, Lisa has also had Epicanthoplasty (lifting the inner eye corners, notice how we can see all of Lisa’s pink tear duct unlike her predebut days) and she has had a cat eye lift. She also got an eyelid surgery to enhance her double eyelid. It also looks like Lisa reshaped her whole lip and got lip fillers (focus on her lips in these photos) :   Lisa lifted the corners of her lips and got lip fillers. These photos also show Lisa’s eyelid surgeries. Her eyelids used to be quite hooded and square, but now her eyelids are prominent and her eyes are very almond shaped, not square shaped. Conclusion All of the Blackpink members have probably had plastic surgery. Apart from their individual surgeries, I also think all four of them had minor skin whitening injections (Glutathione, Lipotocin, Abscorbic Acid, etc.) Surgery or not, Blackpink is beautiful. If they feel more confident now than they were before, than I applaud their decisions to go for surgery! What do you think?

It corrects saggy eyelids or mono-lids to enlarge the eye and removes encroaching tissue from the corners.” Jennie: “ My goodness, what attractive cat eyes she has! She is definitely a natural beauty. The only thing that has changed is her skin tone, she seems fairer. But both tan and fair skin are pretty! I also don’t think that people need to call her out for her skin tone transformation. Her nose used to be flat,wide and bulbous but now she has a cute, upturned and thin nose. You can definitely see the change in her nose if you compare different photos of her when she smiles. She also has had lip fillers, not to make them super filled but to make them smooth and plump and you can definitely see that when she slightly smiles, her lips become uneven and some parts become more bulbous than the other parts. It looks like she has some mini marbles in some parts of her lips if you know what I mean. She has also bleached her skin and uses double eyelid tape because her double eyelids are always placed on different places. I’m fine if you do that to me, but don’t do it to my Mom. You can also see her scars in some photos but I couldn’t find them. Her nose job is actually poorly done and her nostrils deform from time to time. response.answer_text: I’m not a plastic surgeon. If you want an answer from an actual plastic surgeon there’s tons of other answers on this platform. I just wanted to give my input and opinion on this 😅. (first I wanted to say, yes I’m aware that faces change as we grow up. But when it’s a drastic difference, people can assume that it’s due to a cosmetic procedure) Here’s the thing, South Korea is considered the world’s plastic surgery capitol. Plastic surgery is so common and normalized in korea, so as a result, there are many skilled plastic surgeons in korea. The whole point is so it looks natural as well. It’ll be a lot harder to tell the difference between natural features and features that were done in korea because of how skilled and experienced the surgeons are in SK. Knowing this, it’s a lot harder to know which idols went under the knife. Looking at idols through pictures is also a difficult way to know whether they had a procedure or not. Most pictures are edited, and makeup and lighting plays into it as well. People should know all of this before comparing before debut and after debuts of BP or any other idol to see if they got plastic surgery. in my opinion, I can’t say with confidence whether or not Jisoo, Jennie, or Rose got plastic surgery. If they did, it would be a very small procedure. I think Jennie could’ve gotten lip fillers to make her top lips look fuller, but thats also just a speculation because makeup has a lot to do with it. The only member that I rlly think got plastic surgery is Lisa. Her change in her nose is quite obvious.      notice how her nose is. I think she got a nose lift because her nose length and width is still similar. She had a pretty bulbous nose before, but now it’s quite upturned and in some photos her nostrils are quite crooked, an obvious sign of work done.  (This is an example of a nose lift) Look, if you’re a blink or anyone who denys that BP have gone under the knife, I personally think you’re being delusional. Think about it, they’re from a huge company in the Kpop industry in korea. No one would be surprised to know if any of them went under the knife. It’s funny to see blinks denying Lisa got a nose procedure when the proof is all there. No one is saying that BP is any less of a group just because they got plastic surgery, people are just pointing it out. thx for reading my answer. No hate to any of the girls. I’m not against plastic surgery in any way!

response.answer_text: I mean the members of BlackPink said that trainees are banned from having cosmetic surgeries in YG Entertainment in JYP Party’s People. But, that could just be a marketing tactic or a lie. We can’t believe everything that YG says. But it is possible that BlackPink had plastic surgery.  It could just be a makeup effect, or their face changed naturally as they grew older. Or maybe they did get plastic surgery.
